docs.abstract: In an open letter, the social network’s employees said letting politicians post false claims in ads was “a threat” to the company.
docs.snippet: In an open letter, the social network’s employees said letting politicians post false claims in ads was “a threat” to the company.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The letter was aimed at Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, and his top lieutenants. It decried the social network’s recent decision to let politicians post any claims they wanted — even false ones — in ads on the site. It asked Facebook’s leaders to rethink the stance.

headline.main: Dissent Erupts at Facebook Over Hands-Off Stance on Political Ads
